problem: **EditBox by default uses capital letters.**
cocos2d-x version: **v3.9**
platform: **iOS, Android**

Code sample:

```
_emailEditBox = cocos2d::ui::EditBox::create( emailEditBoxBackground->getOriginalSize(),
                                              emailEditBoxBackground );
_emailEditBox->setInputFlag( cocos2d::ui::EditBox::InputFlag::SENSITIVE );
_emailEditBox->setInputMode( cocos2d::ui::EditBox::InputMode::EMAIL_ADDRESS );
_emailEditBox->setReturnType( cocos2d::ui::EditBox::KeyboardReturnType::DONE );
_emailEditBox->setFont( editBoxFontName.c_str(), editBoxFontSize );
_emailEditBox->setFontColor( BROWN );
_emailEditBox->setMaxLength( 50 );
_emailEditBox->setDelegate( this );
```

As a workaround, I set the input flag to SENSITIVE. On iOS this setting makes as a capital letter only for the first character. Unfortunately, **there is no flag to print all characters lowercase.**

![firstletteriscapital](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/5878299/15502090/c34a17b4-21a9-11e6-9bb3-a1c2e6b60b92.png)

On Android, EditBox with SENSITIVE flag shows all letters lowercase, but still SENSITIVE should be used for something else, not for avoiding capital letters.

After invoking 32 times the function "playEffect()" on a SimpleAudioEngine instance you get the message:

`"Fail to play <wav sound name> cause by limited max instance of AudioEngine"`

A test case can be made scheduling this function on the HelloWorld cocos project:

```
void HelloWorld::playSound(float dt) 
{
    auto engine = CocosDenshion::SimpleAudioEngine::getInstance();
    engine->playEffect("yourSound.wav");
}
```

Consider line 45 of file "cocos/editor-support/cocostudio/CocoLoader.cpp":
I think the attribute type should be encoded with cTypeName[] = {'N','F','T','O','A','S','V'};
If the attribute type is 'O', which is an object, then tType = Type(1), which will be a kFalseType.

